[0.845, "o", "\u001b[1m== my-little-claude setup ==\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.330, "o", "  System: RAM: 64.0GB | CPU: 18x aarch64 | GPU: Apple M5 Pro | OS: macos 26.4 | Tier: High\r\n\r\n  Available models (27 total):\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  [coding]\r\n    [T] rnj-1:8b                           8B  5GB  Dense coding model on par with SOTA. Optimized for code and STEM.\r\n    [T] devstral-small-2:24b              24B  16GB  Mistral coding agent. Best-in-class tool use and multi-file editing.\r\n    [T] qwen3-coder:30b-a3b            30B (3B active)  20GB  Alibaba coding MoE. 128K context, strong tool calling, efficient.\r\n    [T] minimax-m2.7                    Large  40GB  MiniMax coding and agentic workflows model.\r\n  ! [T] qwen3-coder-next               80B (3B active)  50GB  Next-gen Qwen coder. 256K context, 3B active params.\r\n  ! [T] devstral-2:123b                  123B  80GB  Mistral's largest coding model. Exceptional agentic capabilities.\r\n\r\n  [general]\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    [T] qwen3.5:0.8b                     0.8B  1GB  Ultra-light. For very constrained environments.\r\n    [ ] llama3.2:1b                        1B  1GB  Meta's tiny Llama. Chat-only, no tool calling.\r\n    [T] qwen3.5:2b                         2B  2GB  Minimal resources. Basic tool calling, fast responses.\r\n    [ ] llama3.2:3b                        3B  2GB  Meta's small Llama. Fast but limited tool calling support.\r\n    [T] ministral-3:3b                     3B  2GB  Mistral tiny edge model. Minimal footprint with tool calling.\r\n"]
[3.017, "o", "\r\n"]
